result.adr_address: 32 High St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 32 High St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: Ying Kee Noodles

reviews.text: It used to be Eng Kee, but Ying Kee was all good too. You can't beat this place. My favorite was yellow egg noodle with roast pork. White flat noodle with beef was yummy too. THEY SPOKE ENGLISH SO DON'T BE AFRAID TO ASK FOR ANYTHING. The lady boss was so nice. She offered scissors to my 7y old nephew to cut the noodles. Was there with my mom and people were friendly. The couple who shared the table with us told us in Cantonese "Ho sek" for beef noodle. It meant delicious!!!
My all-time-favourite barbecued pork noodles!!! Their beef brisket noodle is amazing too!
Great place to get noodle. Love the char siu and fried wanton flat noodle

A classic beef noodles shop on High Street competing with a lot of new cafe and restaurant. The beef brisket is really good that you should have a try. Price is still setting for the neighbor and you will find it value of money.
A local small restaurant serving traditional Cantonese noodles
